'''重力波背景'''（{{lang-en|Gravitational wave background}}，簡稱為'''GWB'''）是在偵測[[重力波|重力波]]上，可能偵測到的目標。偵測到重力波背景將會對早期宇宙的研究及[[高能物理|高能物理]]有深遠的影響。重力波背景即是由天體放出來的重力波會形成一個隨機分布的背景。例如：一個質量夠大的[[恆星|恆星]]在其演化的最終階段會塌陷而形成[[黑洞|黑洞]]或[[中子星|中子星]]，以[[超新星|超新星]]爆炸來說，在其最終階段會有一段快速的塌陷，而此時重力波理論上就會被釋放出來。<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Ott |first1=Christian D. |last2=O'Connor |first2=Evan P. |last3=Gossan |first3=Sarah E. |last4=Abdikamalov |first4=Ernazar |last5=Gamma |first5=Uschi C. T. |last6=Drasco |first6=Steve |display-authors=1 |year=2012 |title=Core-Collapse Supernovae, Neutrinos, and Gravitational Waves |journal=[[Nuclear_Physics_B:_Proceedings_Supplement|Nuclear Physics B: Proceedings Supplement]] |volume=235 |pages=381 |arxiv=1212.4250 |bibcode=2013NuPhS.235..381O |doi=10.1016/j.nuclphysbps.2013.04.036}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Fryer |first1=Chris L. |last2=New |first2=Kimberly C. B. |year=2003 |title=Gravitational Waves from Gravitational Collapse |journal=[[Living_Reviews_in_Relativity|Living Reviews in Relativity]] |volume=6 |issue= |pages= |arxiv= |bibcode= |doi=10.12942/lrr-2003-2}}</ref>此外，在快速旋轉的中子星中，其會受重力波驅使而有不穩定性。

一直以來都有很多研究在進行重力波背景的量測。在2016年2月11號，[[雷射干涉重力波天文台|雷射干涉重力波天文台]]（{{lang|en|LIGO}}）及[[處女座干涉儀|處女座干涉儀]]（{{lang|en|Virgo}}）共同宣布他們於2015年9月時第一次直接觀測到重力波。他們所觀察到的是兩個黑洞碰撞造成的可觀測重力波，這也是要發現重力波背景的第一步。<ref name="Nature_11Feb16">{{cite journal |title=Einstein's gravitational waves found at last |journal=Nature News |url=http://www.nature.com/news/einstein-s-gravitational-waves-found-at-last-1.19361 |date=11 February 2016 |last=Castelvecchi |first=Davide |last2=Witze |first2=Alexandra |doi=10.1038/nature.2016.19361 |accessdate=11 February 2016 |archive-date=2019-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221094833/https://www.nature.com/news/einstein-s-gravitational-waves-found-at-last-1.19361 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Abbott, B.P. |display-authors=et al. |title=Observation of Gravitational Waves from a Binary Black Hole Merger |url=http://journals.aps.org/prl/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevLett.116.061102 |journal=[[Phys._Rev._Lett.|Phys. Rev. Lett.]] |volume=116 |pages=061102 |year=2016 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.116.061102 |arxiv=1602.03837 |bibcode=2016PhRvL.116f1102A |access-date=2016-11-13 |archive-date=2019-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191025233058/https://journals.aps.org/prl/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevLett.116.061102 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==重力波的量測==
[[File:LIGO_measurement_of_gravitational_waves.svg|thumb]]
{{main|重力波天文學}}
2016年2月11號，[[雷射干涉重力波天文台|LIGO]]和{{tsl|en|European Gravitational Observatory|歐洲重力波天文台|EGO}}宣布他們在[[格林威治標準時間|格林威治標準時間]]2015年9月15號10:51時[[重力波天文學|偵測到重力波]]。<ref>{{cite news|title=Gravitational waves from black holes detected|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-35524440|work=BBC News|date=11 February 2016|accessdate=2016-11-13|archive-date=2016-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215204226/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-35524440|dead-url=no}}</ref>此重力波的放出是由於一個29[[太陽質量|太陽質量]]和一個36太陽質量的黑洞，在大約13億[[光年|光年]]外的地方結合成一個62太陽質量的黑洞，而能量等於三太陽質量的重力波被釋放出來。<ref name="Wired">[http://www.wired.com/2016/02/scientists-spot-the-gravity-waves-that-flex-the-universe/ LIGO’s First-Ever Detection of Gravitational Waves Opens a New Window on the Universe] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216081133/http://www.wired.com/2016/02/scientists-spot-the-gravity-waves-that-flex-the-universe/ |date=2016-02-16 }}</ref>LIGO在漢福德區和利文斯頓的兩個偵測器都有偵測到這個重力波訊號，其中，因為與波源夾角不同的關係，此兩偵測器偵測到的時間差了7微秒。此訊號源在[[南半天球|南半天球]]，大略的方位是在[[麥哲倫雲|麥哲倫雲]]的位置，但較麥哲倫雲來的遠許多。<ref name="Nature_11Feb16" />羅徹斯特理工學院指出<ref>{{Cite news |publisher=[[Rochester_Institute_of_Technology|Rochester Institute of Technology]] |title=LIGO Confirms RIT's Breakthrough Prediction of Gravitational Waves |url=http://www.sciencenewsline.com/news/2016021121020059.html |work=Science Newsline – Space & Planetary |date=11 February 2016 |access-date=2016-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625120852/http://sciencenewsline.com/news/2016021121020059.html# |archive-date=2016-06-25 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>這個研究的信心水準來到99.99994%<ref name="Wired" /> 
==未來展望==
未來的[[重力波探測器|重力波探測]]希望能找到早期的重力波及宇宙形成之初所留下的證據，以期能夠知道[[大霹靂|大霹靂]]是否發生超過一次。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-35524440|title=Einstein's gravitational waves 'seen' from black holes|publisher=BBC News|author=Pallab Ghosh|date=2016-02-11|accessdate=2016-11-13|archive-date=2016-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160212222326/http://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-35524440|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-future-of-gravitational-wave-astronomy/|title=The Future of Gravitational Wave Astronomy|publisher=Scientific American|author=Lee Billings|date=2016-02-12|accessdate=2016-11-13|archive-date=2016-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506104020/http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-future-of-gravitational-wave-astronomy/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

